[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0;32m╔════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[0;32m║  Agentic Development Workflow + Harness Engineering Demo          ║\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[0;32m║  에이전틱 개발 워크플로우 + 하네스 엔지니어링 데모               ║\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0;32m║                                                                    ║\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[0;32m║  Part 1: Design Phase (Brainstorm → Plan)                         ║\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0;32m║  파트 1: 설계 단계 (브레인스토밍 → 계획 작성)                     ║\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[0;32m╚════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.011, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0;36m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1m  1. Agentic Development Playbook — 4-Phase Workflow / 4단계 워크플로우\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0;36m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1;37mThe playbook defines a human-in-the-loop workflow:\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;37m플레이북은 사람이 참여하는(human-in-the-loop) 워크플로우를 정의합니다:\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\r\n  │                                                                │\r\n  │   \u001b[1mPhase 1: Design\u001b[0m        Brainstorm → Spec → Plan            │\r\n  │   \u001b[2m설계 단계\u001b[0m              브레인스토밍 → 명세 → 계획            │\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  │                          ↓                                     │\r\n  │   \u001b[1mPhase 2: Execute\u001b[0m       Implement plan step-by-step         │\r\n  │   \u001b[2m실행 단계\u001b[0m              계획을 단계별로 구현                   │\r\n  │                          ↓                                     │\r\n  │   \u001b[1mPhase 3: Review\u001b[0m        Code review + CI feedback           │\r\n  │   \u001b[2m리뷰 단계\u001b[0m              코드 리뷰 + CI 피드백                 │\r\n  │                          ↓                                     │\r\n  │   \u001b[1mPhase 4: Validate\u001b[0m      Tests + security + deploy           │\r\n  │   \u001b[2m검증 단계\u001b[0m              테스트 + 보안 + 배포                   │\r\n  │                                                                │\r\n  │   \u001b[1;33mHuman reviews and approves at each phase transition\u001b[0m        │\r\n  │   \u001b[1;33m사람이 각 단계 전환 시 검토하고 승인합니다\u001b[0m                  │\r\n  │         "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                       │\r\n  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\r\n"]
[6.018, "o", "\r\n\u001b[0;36m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1m  2. Key Design Principles / 핵심 설계 원칙\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[0;36m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1;37m1. Start simple, add complexity only when needed\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[2m   단순하게 시작하고, 필요할 때만 복잡성을 추가\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1;37m2. Workflows vs. Agents — know the difference\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[2m   워크플로우 vs. 에이전트 — 차이를 이해\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1;37m3. Orchestration over prompt engineering\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[2m   프롬프트 엔지니어링보다 오케스트레이션이 중요\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1;37m4. Minimal freedom principle\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[2m   최소 자유 원칙 — 결과를 달성하는 최소한의 자율성 부여\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1;37m5. Reflection — agent reviews its own work\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m   자기 성찰 — 에이전트가 자신의 결과물을 스스로 검토\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1;37m6. Developers must understand the code they approve\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[2m   개발자는 승인하는 코드를 반드시 이해해야 한다\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[6.011, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0;36m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1m  3. Phase 1: Brainstorming → Spec / 브레인스토밍 → 명세서\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0;36m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[2mIn Claude Code, the developer starts with:\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2mClaude Code에서 개발자가 다음 명령으로 시작:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1;33m> /brainstorming\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1;33m> Add a Quote of the Day REST API with list, random, and ID lookup.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[2.019, "o", "  \u001b[1;37mThe AI agent explores requirements through Q&A:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1;37mAI 에이전트가 Q&A를 통해 요구사항을 탐색합니다:\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  \u001b[2m  Q: Should we use a database or in-memory storage?\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m     데이터베이스를 사용할까요, 인메모리 저장소를 사용할까요?\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[0;32m  A: In-memory for now. Keep it simple.\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[0;32m     지금은 인메모리로. 단순하게 유지.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  \u001b[2m  Q: What data model? Record or POJO?\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m     데이터 모델은? Record? POJO?\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[0;32m  A: Java 21 Record — immutable, concise.\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[0;32m     Java 21 Record — 불변, 간결.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[2m  Q: Categories for the quotes?\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m     명언 카테고리는?\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[0;32m  A: programming, inspiration — configurable default.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[0;32m     programming, inspiration — 기본값은 설정 가능.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[5.020, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1;37m→ AI generates the spec:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1;37m→ AI가 명세서를 생성합니다:\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1;33m$ cat docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-18-DEMO-001-quote-api.md\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.030, "o", "# Spec: Quote of the Day API\r\n\r\n**Ticket:** DEMO-001\r\n**Date:** 2026-04-18\r\n**Status:** Approved\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\nAdd a \"Quote of the Day\" REST API to the Quarkus application, providing\r\nendpoints to list, retrieve, and randomly select motivational quotes.\r\n\r\n## Requirements\r\n\r\n### Functional Requirements\r\n\r\n1. `GET /api/quotes` — return all quotes, optionally filtered by `?category=`\r\n2. `GET /api/quotes/random` — return a single random quote\r\n3. `GET /api/quotes/{id}` — return a quote by ID, or 404 if not found\r\n4. Quotes are stored in-memory (no database required for this iteration)\r\n5. Each quote has: `id`, `text`, `author`, `category`\r\n\r\n### Non-Functional Requirements\r\n\r\n- JSON responses via Jackson serialization\r\n- Logging via `org.jboss.logging.Logger` (no System.out)\r\n- Configuration via `@ConfigProperty` for default category\r\n- Full test coverage with `@QuarkusTest` and REST Assured\r\n\r\n## Design Decisions\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[4.016, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[0;32m✓ Human reviews and approves the spec\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[0;32m✓ 사람이 명세서를 검토하고 승인합니다\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.019, "o", "\r\n\u001b[0;36m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1m  4. Phase 1 (cont): Spec → Plan / 명세서 → 구현 계획\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[0;36m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[2mIn Claude Code:\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1;33m> /writing-plans\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;33m> Create implementation plan from the approved spec.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[2.017, "o", "  \u001b[1;37m→ AI generates the implementation plan:\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;37m→ AI가 구현 계획을 생성합니다:\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1;33m$ cat docs/superpowers/plans/2026-04-18-DEMO-001-quote-api.md\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.041, "o", "# Plan: Quote of the Day API\r\n\r\n**Ticket:** DEMO-001\r\n**Spec:** [2026-04-18-DEMO-001-quote-api.md](../specs/2026-04-18-DEMO-001-quote-api.md)\r\n**Date:** 2026-04-18\r\n**Model hints:** Sonnet for Tasks 1-2 (mechanical), Opus for Tasks 3-4 (logic)\r\n\r\n## Task Sequence\r\n\r\n### Task 1: Add Jackson dependency\r\n- **File:** `pom.xml`\r\n- **Action:** Add `quarkus-rest-jackson` dependency\r\n- **Verify:** `./mvnw compile -q`\r\n\r\n### Task 2: Create Quote Record DTO\r\n- **File:** `src/main/java/dev/tedwon/Quote.java`\r\n- **Action:** Create Java 21 Record with fields: `id`, `text`, `author`, `category`\r\n- **Verify:** `./mvnw compile -q`\r\n\r\n### Task 3: Create QuoteService CDI bean\r\n- **Files:**\r\n  - `src/main/java/dev/tedwon/QuoteService.java`\r\n  - `src/main/resources/application.properties`\r\n  - `src/test/java/dev/tedwon/QuoteServiceTest.java`\r\n- **Action:**\r\n  - `@ApplicationScoped` service with in-memory quote data\r\n  - `@ConfigProperty(name = \"app.quote.default-category\")` injection\r\n  - `org.jboss.logging.Logger` for all loggi"]
[0.000, "o", "ng\r\n  - Methods: `getAllQuotes()`, `getQuoteById(long)`, `getRandomQuote()`, `getQuotesByCategory(String)`\r\n  - Unit tests for each method\r\n- **Verify:** `./mvnw test -q`\r\n\r\n### Task 4: Create QuoteResource REST endpoints\r\n- **Files:**\r\n  - `src/main/java/dev/tedwon/QuoteResource.java`\r\n  - `src/test/java/dev/tedwon/QuoteResourceTest.java`\r\n  - `src/test/java/dev/tedwon/QuoteResourceIT.java`\r\n- **Action:**\r\n  - `@Path(\"/api/quotes\")` with 3 GET endpoints\r\n  - Category query param filtering on list endpoint\r\n  - 404 handling via `jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response`\r\n  - `@QuarkusTest` with REST Assured for all endpoints\r\n  - Integration test extending QuoteResourceTest\r\n- **Verify:** `./mvnw test`\r\n\r\n### Task 5: Final verification\r\n- **Action:**\r\n  - `./mvnw spotless:apply` then `./mvnw spotless:check -q`\r\n  - `./mvnw verify`\r\n  - Manual curl test against `./mvnw quarkus:dev`\r\n- **Verify:** All 7 harness checks pass\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\n\r\n```\r\nTask 1 (Jackson) ──► Task 2 (Record) ──► Task 3 (Service) ─"]
[0.000, "o", "─► Task 4 (Resource) ──► Task 5 (Verify)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAll tasks are sequential — each builds on the previous.\r\n\r\n## Harness Integration\r\n\r\nThe pre-commit harness runs 7 automated checks on every commit:\r\n- BUILD-01: Compilation\r\n- BUILD-02: Tests\r\n- BUILD-03: Code formatting (Spotless)\r\n- QUAL-01: No System.out.println\r\n- QUAL-02: No hardcoded secrets\r\n- CONV-01: Conventional commit messages\r\n- CONV-02: Test coverage for @Path classes\r\n\r\nAny violation blocks the commit with actionable error messages.\r\nThe agent reads the errors, fixes all violations, and retries.\r\n"]
[5.012, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[0;32m✓ Human reviews task sequence and dependencies\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "  \u001b[0;32m✓ 사람이 작업 순서와 의존성을 검토합니다\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  \u001b[0;32m✓ Plan saved as versioned artifact (audit trail)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[0;32m✓ 계획이 버전 관리 산출물로 저장됩니다 (감사 추적)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.014, "o", "\r\n"]
